  "body": "As a user\r\nI want to be able to create an encrypted community\r\nSo that I can make sure nobody who's not a member can read the messages\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nWe just added support for encrypted communities, the user should be presented with a checkbox that allows to enable encryption when creating the community.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-go/blob/eb4ab9316cc0f0ba07b01b4177bd50bdfc3ae33a/protocol/requests/create_community_request.go#L46 can be set to `true` if the checkbox is enabled.\r\n\r\nOnly communities with a concept of membership should have this option (regardless of whether is manual or automatic approval)",
